    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 2: TURBOCHARGERS - INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSPECTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CLEANING</title>
            <para>Clean these components as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                        USE A CAUSTIC SOLUTION ON TURBOCHARGER OR TUBES.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thoroughly clean the piping connecting the air cleaner to the turbocharger with soap and
                    water. Dry with filtered compressed air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the vehicle mounted air cleaner and clean inside the air cleaner element housing.
                    (Helps prevent turbocharger or engine failure.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean air inlet piping and connecting hoses with filtered compressed air.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect oil inlet tube and oil drain tube for restrictions. Clean with a suitable
                    solvent and a nylon brush. Dry using filtered compressed air.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
